radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal bilateral dependent atelectasis, right greater than left; a 4-mm hypodensity in the left hepatic lobe; additional tiny hepatic hypodensities measuring up to 7 mm; the liver is otherwise unremarkable; appendix is fluid filled and dilated to 9 mm with marked periappendiceal fat stranding; small quantity of free fluid in the right lower abdominal quadrant; unremarkable gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, kidneys; small quantity of free fluid in the pelvis; multilevel degenerative changes of the lumbar spine noted.
